Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.36,0:04:36.22,1080P_CN_Up,,0,0,0,,字幕翻译给虫，欢迎投币点赞收藏分享转发关注评论充电~
Dialogue: 1,0:00:02.12,0:00:08.62,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,1977年，旅行者1号探测器发射升空，去探索外太阳系的秘密
Dialogue: 2,0:00:02.12,0:00:08.62,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,In 1977, the Voyager 1 space probe was launched to study the outer solar system.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:09.17,0:00:14.54,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,两枚旅行者号探测器成为人类航天史上运行时间最长的探测器
Dialogue: 2,0:00:09.17,0:00:14.54,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,The two Voyager space probes have become the longest operating spacecrafts in spaceflight history.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:15.22,0:00:24.46,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,41年后，旅行者1号距离地球190亿公里，速度每小时61000公里
Dialogue: 2,0:00:15.22,0:00:24.46,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,41 years later, Voyager 1 is now 19 Billion kilometres from Earth and travelling at 61,000km/h.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:24.94,0:00:28.48,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,虽然旅行者1号是至今离地球最远的人造物体
Dialogue: 2,0:00:24.94,0:00:28.48,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Despite Voyager 1 being the furthest man made object from Earth,
Dialogue: 1,0:00:28.60,0:00:32.88,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,我们仍然能和它进行例行通讯
Dialogue: 2,0:00:28.60,0:00:32.88,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,we are still able to communicate with the space probe on a regular basis.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:33.28,0:00:37.44,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,但在我们联系不到它之前，它最远能到哪里？
Dialogue: 2,0:00:33.28,0:00:37.44,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,But how far can it go before we can no longer communicate with it?
Dialogue: 1,0:00:39.16,0:00:45.74,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,要回答这个问题，我们得知道它如何在210亿公里外接收并发送数据
Dialogue: 2,0:00:39.16,0:00:45.74,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,To answer this, we need to know how Voyager 1 receives and transmits data from 21 Billion Kilometres away.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:46.46,0:00:51.40,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,地球会以20千瓦的功率向旅行者号发送无线电信号
Dialogue: 2,0:00:46.46,0:00:51.40,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,A 20 KiloWatt signal is transmitted from Earth to Voyager 1 using radio waves.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:51.92,0:00:55.78,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,信号要经过近20小时才能到达探测器
Dialogue: 2,0:00:51.92,0:00:55.78,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,It takes almost 20 hours for the signal to reach the space probe
Dialogue: 1,0:00:55.82,0:00:58.30,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,探测器敏感的天线会接收到信号
Dialogue: 2,0:00:55.82,0:00:58.30,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,where it’s sensitive antenna picks up the signal.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:58.98,0:01:05.08,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,作为对比，火星车平均只要15分钟就能把信息传回地球
Dialogue: 2,0:00:58.98,0:01:05.08,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,For comparison, it takes the rovers on Mars an average of just 15 minutes to send messages back to Earth.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:05.86,0:01:09.84,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,而旅行者号把数据发回地球所用的信号功率有20瓦
Dialogue: 2,0:01:05.86,0:01:09.84,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Voyager starts sending data back to Earth using a 20 Watt signal.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:10.40,0:01:13.64,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,信号在穿越茫茫太空的时候会不断衰减
Dialogue: 2,0:01:10.40,0:01:13.64,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,As it travels through space, the signal strength weakens.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:13.64,0:01:17.26,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,等到达地球，信号就已经相当微弱了
Dialogue: 2,0:01:13.64,0:01:17.26,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,And by the time it reaches Earth, the signal is barely detectable.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:18.00,0:01:21.16,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,想和这种距离的探测器通信
Dialogue: 2,0:01:18.00,0:01:21.16,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,In order to communicate with objects that are this far away,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:21.38,0:01:24.16,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,信号有多强已经不重要了
Dialogue: 2,0:01:21.38,0:01:24.16,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,it doesn’t really matter how strong the signal is,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:24.26,0:01:27.96,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,只要你的接收端足够的灵敏就行了
Dialogue: 2,0:01:24.26,0:01:27.96,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,as long as you have a receiver that is sensitive enough to pick it up.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:29.14,0:01:36.10,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,NASA使用的是均匀分布在地球的三组天线构成的深空网络(DSN)
Dialogue: 2,0:01:29.14,0:01:36.10,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,NASA uses the Deep Space Network which consists of three Antenna complexes equally spaced around the Earth.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:36.68,0:01:42.68,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,每一组天线包含70米天线外加多个34米天线
Dialogue: 2,0:01:36.68,0:01:42.68,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Each complex has a huge 70 metre antenna along with multiple 34 metre antennae
Dialogue: 1,0:01:42.68,0:01:49.38,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,组合起来能接收到比我们平常调频广播信号弱数千倍的信号
Dialogue: 2,0:01:42.68,0:01:49.38,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,which can be combined to pick up signals that are thousands of times weaker than your standard FM radio signal.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:50.00,0:01:56.22,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,DSN每天会花几小时的时间接收来自旅行者1号的信号
Dialogue: 2,0:01:50.00,0:01:56.22,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,The Deep Space Network spends several hours each day listening for faint signals from Voyager 1,
Dialogue: 1,0:01:56.56,0:01:59.92,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,到目前为止，探测器仍然在与我们“交流”
Dialogue: 2,0:01:56.56,0:01:59.92,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,and so far, it continues to talk back to us.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:00.82,0:02:06.34,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,50年来，我们探测信号的技术有了长足的进步
Dialogue: 2,0:02:00.82,0:02:06.34,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Since our methods for detecting signals has improved drastically over the past 50 years,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:06.50,0:02:11.16,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,所以还真不好说我们到底能和太空中多远的物体交流
Dialogue: 2,0:02:06.50,0:02:11.16,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,there isn’t really a limit on how far we can communicate with objects in Space.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:11.74,0:02:17.22,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,以现有科技，我们能和若干光年外的物体建立可靠通信
Dialogue: 2,0:02:11.74,0:02:17.22,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,With our current technology, we could reliably communicate with objects that are many light years away from us,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:17.48,0:02:23.42,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,只要我们的接收端足够灵敏精准来接收极其微弱的信号
Dialogue: 2,0:02:17.48,0:02:23.42,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,as long as our receivers are sensitive and accurate enough to pick up the extremely weak signals.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:24.98,0:02:31.42,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,随着旅行者号离我们越来越远，信号往返所需时间就越来越长
Dialogue: 2,0:02:24.98,0:02:31.42,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,As Voyager travels further and further away from Earth it takes longer to send and receive signals.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:31.92,0:02:35.86,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,信号强度也会逐渐减弱，数据率也跟着下降
Dialogue: 2,0:02:31.92,0:02:35.86,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,The signal strength also gets weaker and data rates become slower
Dialogue: 1,0:02:36.00,0:02:39.38,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,使得与探测器通信难度越来越大
Dialogue: 2,0:02:36.00,0:02:39.38,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,making it harder and harder to communicate with the spacecraft.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:40.36,0:02:43.86,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,旅行者1号的旅程还会无限进行下去
Dialogue: 2,0:02:40.36,0:02:43.86,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Voyager 1 will continue on it’s journey indefinitely,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:44.14,0:02:48.30,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,虽然我们与它没有通信的限制
Dialogue: 2,0:02:44.14,0:02:48.30,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,and although there is technically no limit to how far we can communicate,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:48.48,0:02:52.68,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,但我们和它的通信也剩不了几年了
Dialogue: 2,0:02:48.48,0:02:52.68,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,our communication with Voyager 1 only has a few years left.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:53.40,0:02:58.78,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,因为旅行者1号是核电池动力的，它的电功率每天都在衰减
Dialogue: 2,0:02:53.40,0:02:58.78,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Since Voyager 1 is Nuclear powered, it’s electrical power weakens each day.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:59.61,0:03:02.38,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,在1990年，为了节省功率
Dialogue: 2,0:02:59.61,0:03:02.38,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,In 1990, in order to save power,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:02.38,0:03:09.32,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,工程师在旅行者号拍完“暗淡蓝点”那张照片之后关闭了它的相机
Dialogue: 2,0:03:02.38,0:03:09.32,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,engineers turned off the spacecraft’s camera after Voyager took the famous “Pale Blue Dot” image,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:09.42,0:03:14.42,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,照片中的地球只是茫茫宇宙深色背景中的一个蓝色像素点
Dialogue: 2,0:03:09.42,0:03:14.42,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,which showed Earth as a tiny blue pixel against the darkness of space.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:15.10,0:03:20.74,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,今天，旅行者1号上11个科学仪器只有4个还在运转
Dialogue: 2,0:03:15.10,0:03:20.74,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Today, only 4 out of the 11 scientific instruments on Voyager 1 are still active.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:21.46,0:03:29.22,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,这些仪器用于收集太阳系外围的电磁场、太阳风、宇宙射线等数据
Dialogue: 2,0:03:21.46,0:03:29.22,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,These instruments are being used to collect data on magnetic fields, solar winds and cosmic rays outside of our solar system.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:30.68,0:03:38.12,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,旅行者1号将在大约八年内彻底耗尽电能，再也无法保持仪器的运转
Dialogue: 2,0:03:30.68,0:03:38.12,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,In around 8 years, Voyager 1 will completely run out of power and will no longer be able to keep it’s instruments going.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:38.90,0:03:44.56,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,科学家会继续与探测器通信，收集它探测的重要信息
Dialogue: 2,0:03:38.90,0:03:44.56,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Scientists will continue to communicate with the space probe and receive the important information it gathers
Dialogue: 1,0:03:44.78,0:03:47.92,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,直到它发送完最后一比特数据
Dialogue: 2,0:03:44.78,0:03:47.92,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,until it eventually sends its last bit of data
Dialogue: 1,0:03:48.08,0:03:53.46,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,然后永远淹没在浩瀚宇宙之中
Dialogue: 2,0:03:48.08,0:03:53.46,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,and disappears silently into space, never to be heard from ever again.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:54.54,0:03:58.42,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,尽管旅行者号太空探测器大限将至
Dialogue: 2,0:03:54.54,0:03:58.42,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,So although the end is near for the Voyager space probes,
Dialogue: 1,0:03:58.64,0:04:04.34,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,但它传奇的旅程与其教会我们的宝贵知识仍然让我们受益匪浅
Dialogue: 2,0:03:58.64,0:04:04.34,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,we can appreciate the incredible journey they have been on and the valuable science they have taught us.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:05.36,0:04:10.16,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,感谢观看本期Primal Space，感谢赞助者们对每个视频的帮助
Dialogue: 2,0:04:05.36,0:04:10.16,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Thank you to the Primal Space Patrons who help to write and research each video.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:10.67,0:04:16.44,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,想资瓷的人可以去Patreon资瓷，地址在下方
Dialogue: 2,0:04:10.67,0:04:16.44,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,If you'd like to contribute to Primal Space, please visit Patreon.com/PrimalSpace,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:16.80,0:04:22.84,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,满50位赞助者后赠送土星五号乐高模型哦
Dialogue: 2,0:04:16.80,0:04:22.84,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,where we will be doing a giveaway of a Saturn V Lego set once we reach 50 Patrons.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:23.22,0:04:31.62,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,所以记得关注，一起讨论、学习一个太空姿势
Dialogue: 2,0:04:23.22,0:04:31.62,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,So make sure you're subscribed, so you can join the discussion as we continue to learn more about all things space.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:31.86,0:04:36.22,1080P_CN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,感谢观看，下期见
Dialogue: 2,0:04:31.86,0:04:36.22,1080P_EN_Bottom,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much for watching and I'll see you in the next video.
